OL,3,CCouncils warn Chancellor that support
OL,4,Cfor most vulnerable is under threat
OL,6,FAccording to the document, the LGA has
OL,7,Fdrawn up analysis showing that English
OL,8,Fcouncils face a funding gap of #2.3
OL,9,Fbillion in 2025/26, rising to #3.9
OL,10,Fbillion in 2026/27 and then #6.2
OL,11,Fbillion after that. It warns that
OL,12,Fcouncils are increasingly reliant on
OL,13,Ftheir financial reserves to balance
OL,14,Fbudgets.
OL,16,FThey are urging Reeves to deliver a
OL,17,F"significant and sustained increase"
OL,18,Fin funding, particularly into adult
OL,19,Fand children's social care, special
OL,20,Fneeds, home to school transport and
OL,21,Ftemporary accommodation.
